    <text id="B0303T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McDonnell settles accounts with Jackson over Bureau property before Jackson
                    leaves and John Jordan takes over as agent in Staunton.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R.F. &amp;
                        A.L.</abbr><lb/>Head <abbr expan="Quarters">Qrs.</abbr> 9th Sub <abbr
                            expan="District">Dist.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient">Mr Thos. P. Jackson<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner">A.S.A.Comr</abbr><lb/>Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-03-23"><abbr expan="March 23, 1868">Mch 23/68</abbr></date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>The following is a list of the articles of Bureau property for which I hold your
                        <unclear>Memo</unclear> Receipts. Viz:</p>

                <p>2 office desks, 4 chairs<lb/>1 heating stove, 1 Horse<lb/>2 Riding Saddles -
                    condition good<lb/>2 <abbr expan="Riding">"</abbr> Bridles <abbr
                        expan="Condition good">"</abbr><lb/> 2 Saddle blankets - much worn<lb/>1
                    Head Halter <unclear>So-</unclear></p>

                <p>On the reception of receipt from <abbr expan="Colonel">Col.</abbr> Jordan for the
                    above mentioned articles the memo receipts will be returned and a certificate of
                    non-accountability for property in this Sub <abbr expan="District">Dist.</abbr>
                    furnished.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="Obedient">Obedt</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Servant">St</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>John A. McDonnell<lb/>Sub <abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst
                        Comr</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
